Here's a simple C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file. This program uses basic file I/O operations and string manipulation functions.

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::ifstream file("input.txt"); // Replace with your input file path
    std::string targetWord = "example"; // Replace with the word you want to count
    int count = 0;
    std::string line;

    if (!file.is_open()) {
        std::cerr << "Error opening file." << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }

    while (getline(file, line)) {
        size_t pos = 0;
        while ((pos = line.find(targetWord, pos)) != std::string::npos) {
            ++count;
            pos += targetWord.length();
        }
    }

    std::cout << "The word '" << targetWord << "' appears " << count
                << " times in the file." << std::endl;

    file.close();
    return 0;
}
```

To use this program:
1. Replace `"input.txt"` with the path to your text file.
2. Replace `"example"` with the word you wish to search for and count its occurrences.

Please note that this program is case-sensitive and does not handle punctuation well. If you need case-insensitive counting or better handling of punctuation, you'll need to modify the code accordingly.
